profile:
Home Painters Toronto

If you're looking for a professional painting and home renovation company with years of experience to prove it, then look no further, Home Painters Toronto is the contractor for you. We specialize in interior, exterior, residential, and commercial painting and our services don't stop there! We can also help you with drywall repair and installation, plaster, stucco ceiling repair and removal, carpentry, Kitchen Cabinet repainting, hardwood flooring and much more! Call one of our customer service experts now and be well on your way to a quote and a beautifully transformed property.

Serving Toronto and the regional Municipalities of York, Halton, Peel, Durham, and more!   

Remember when you go with Home Painters we value your business and referrals and are committed to getting it done right the first time. GUARANTEED!

Why use Home Painters to paint your house/office?
•Two Year Guarantee On All Work Done
•Full Workers Compensation
•5 Million Liability Insurance
•Fully Bonded Workers (Criminal Background Checks on ALL Workers)
•30 Years Experience in the Painting Industry
•Thousands of Satisfied Clients
•Top Quality Paints Used Including Benjamin Moore, Dulux, Behr, Sherwin Williams, Para etc
•Drop sheets to Protect Your Floors and Belongings
•100% Satisfaction Guaranteed!!

 Interior Painting Services Include:
•Painting (i.e. walls, trim, doors, floors, ceilings, etc.)
•Staining (i.e. banisters, hardwood floors, cabinets, etc.)
•Faux finishing  
•Stucco Painting and Repair
•Wallpapering and Removal 
•Drywall Repair and Replacement
•Plaster

 Exterior Painting Services Include:
•Painting Exterior Surfaces (ie. windows, brick, doors, eaves, soffits, aluminum siding, etc.)
•Deck/Fence Staining and Refinishing
•Power Washing 
•Caulking 
•Rotten Wood Replacement/Repair

profile:
We are here to simplify the shed buying and installation experience. Experts on what brands and models are the best each year, we will guide you to the right product that best meets your needs. A product you can trust in that will provide you with many years of worry free backyard storage. 


We have been specializing in shed foundations for more than a decade. Whether it be concrete or wood, we will deliver a reliable base that looks great and is built to last. Concrete has the advantage of being animal proof, it can be made with a lower profile to the ground, and will last for 30+ years maintenance-free. Our wood foundations are developed to provide a cost effective option while maintaining integrity against animals, and the wear and tear from the elements.  While they are not 100% animal proof, they are highly resistant! We have designed them to be low to the ground, only about 7", less than the average step. They will last 20+ years.

We have always had attention to detail, as is clear in our reviews on HomeStars, Google, Yellow Pages and other places on the web. What brings us joy and pleasure is doing the best job we can for you. We only hire the best to bring you the best, each is fully trained and most have been with us for many years. We pride ourselves on providing the highest quality service for all your shed need's. We have seen a lot of wood bases and concrete bases built by other companies, far more often than not they are not perfectly level, square, or custom sized for your shed and lack attractiveness. A lot of attention goes into the details of building a foundation that is just right for your model of shed. It’s one of the biggest mistakes one can make when hiring someone to install their shed foundation. Countless times we see how poorly constructed bases fail, and many times homeowners call us to rip out a foundation because it is falling apart after just a couple years or they choose to live with a failing base in order to save the cost of having it rebuilt. 


We are the exclusive shed company that is trusted to build the display sheds for Costco and Lowe's in Southern Ontario. We have installed thousands of these sheds for these stores and for the homeowner’s that buy them for their backyards. No one is more familiar with the installation and these products in Canada then us. We take pride in our work, and it show's. We guarantee that your shed, play set or gazebo will be assembled professionally and we back that up with a lifetime warranty on our workmanship. 


 Our rates are lower then the big box stores and are installed by someone with far more experience! Why have a sub-contractor or handyman that may not have ever built a shed in their life do your installation? They certainly don’t specialize in shed foundations, we know because we have ripped many of them out soon after they left. 


Our primary coverage area is the Greater Toronto area, as far west as Hamilton, east to Oshawa, and north to Newmarket. We will travel further for a travel expense, please contact us for more information.

profile:
At Delco Windows and Doors we understand that your home is your biggest investment, so when its time to renovate your home only the best will do.
 
We specialize in the replacement and installation of vinyl windows, steel and fiberglass doors, patio and storm doors and porch enclosures in Toronto and the entire GTA.
We are factory-direct, eliminating the middleman so that we can provide the most competitive pricing available. We provide the finest products using the latest machinery, craftsmanship and technologies. Our products have some of the best warranties available including the lifetime transferrable warranty. Whether you are looking for vinyl windows, a beautiful fiberglass front door or an efficient patio door you will get the best value for your buck, installed by our quality installers with many years of experience and customer service that is second to none.
 
Giving customers more value for their money, providing excellent customer service and quality reliable products has been our winning formula for many years and we look forward to continue to service our valued customers for many more.

profile:
I’m Bryan Smit, and I run this business with my family and close friends. I have been working as a carpenter for eight years in the Greater Toronto Hamilton Area, but have a lifetime of experience in home renovations and the skilled trades.
 
Both of my grandfathers built new lives for their families in Canada as tradesmen—one as a plumber, and one as a mechanic and handyman. As active members in the Dutch community in Southern Ontario, both quickly became known as reliable and skilled labourers always willing to help out with anything from a clogged toilet to a full renovation. That dedication to quality work, that love for working with your hands and providing for your family and the families in your community, has been passed down in my family for generations. My father is a plumber; my brother is a welder; my uncles and cousins work in construction and woodworking; and we always come together when one of us has a project, whether it’s redoing a roof, building a shed, or renovating a bathroom. Combined, we have over 200 years of building, renovation, and repair experience.
 
From a very young age, my parents involved my siblings and me in the family projects, and they instilled in me a passion for constructing something, for the accuracy and attention to detail required, for the feeling of contributing to what makes a family’s house a home.
 
From basements to bedrooms to backyards, Bryan Smit’s Carpentry will help make your house the home your family dreamed of.
 
All of our work is fully bonded and insured.

Follow us on Instagram! https://www.instagram.com/bryansmitcarpentry/
name: Bryan Smit's Carpentry

profile: I started from an artistic background, coming from OCAD in the early 90's to working as a Scenic Artist/Carpenter and Prop/Backdrops/Set Builder in the film/TV industry. I have a very good understanding of the way materials work and how they should be used, along with solid custom woodworking skills I have gained over the past 30yrs . My website shows both my artistry and custom build skills - they all come together one way or another. I am known for my finishing and good eye for detail. Please see my picture gallery for reference.
service_area: I service mostly mid - uptown areas but will travel if required.
products: I use only good quality products that have gained my trust over the years.
services: My services are: Paint/Stain and Plastering/Drywall/Taping- that includes restoration of old houses and new construction. I am a magician at hiding damages (no wallpaper or stucco). Woodworking - such as deck, stairs, railing, fences, porch code upgrading. Custom builds for personal use. Consult with design options. I can solve/troubleshoot difficult problems in certain situations. Water leak detection and restoration. Tiles, design & paint murals and window film treatments. Installer of many products. Basic wiring and plumbing too etc..
specialities: My specialties would be keeping an eye on the details as they can become overlooked and the over-all finish of the project at hand. I can help design & advise on small custom builds and paint/stain choices. Re-use, Re-claim or Re-purpose if necessary. I don't take liberties and give 100%. I also have a Home Inspectors certificate which gives me added knowledge to advise clients and troubleshoot issues & problems.

profile:
ABOUT SHANDYMAN CONTRACTING

ShandyMan Contracting is one of Toronto's most trusted General Contractors, specializing in Roofing, Painting and Carpentry & Renovations.

Whether it be a commercial or residential design or repair, The ShandyMan Team prides themselves on their results and happy customers.

CORE VALUES

PEOPLE
This core value runs deep in the Shand family - passed down from Shane’s father who worked very hard to leave a legacy worth following. You can see it on the faces of friends, family, employees and customers of ShandyMan Contracting Inc. Love and leadership is at the centre of this organization.

PASSION
One has to be passionate about their craft in order to be successful in this business - it can be tough and the work isn’t always pretty. For anyone who’s ever worked with "The ShandyMan", the first thing you’ll notice is his passion for life, family and work. Passion is wildly reflected in ShandyMan Contracting’s long lasting relationships and successful projects across the Greater Toronto Area.

PURPOSE
Founder, Shane Shand truly believes in living a life of purpose and meaning. ShandyMan Contracting provides that opportunity for its employees through the example Shane and his team have been setting from an early age. Growing up in Toronto’s Beaches, and learning from his father, he now brings over 20 years of experience as a General Contractor with key specialities. Shane is now able to live out his own dream through the art of enhancing commercial and residential properties.

SHANE SHAND
FOUNDER & PRESIDENT

THE SHANDYMAN STORY
MEET OUR FOUNDER & PRESIDENT SHANE SHAND THE "SHANDYMAN"
Born and raised in Toronto's Beaches Community, Shane and his team bring over 20 years of experience in residential and commercial General Contracting. ShandyMan Contracting services a variety of clients across the Greater Toronto Area and beyond. Specialties include; roofing, painting and carpentry. ShandyMan's mission, vision and core values are the guide to transforming your space.

EVERY DAY IS A BLESSED DAY.

profile: I started from an artistic background, coming from OCAD in the early 90's to working as a Scenic Artist/Carpenter and Prop/Backdrops/Set Builder in the film/TV industry. I have a very good understanding of the way materials work and how they should be used, along with solid custom woodworking skills I have gained over the past 30yrs . My website shows both my artistry and custom build skills - they all come together one way or another. I am known for my finishing and good eye for detail. Please see my picture gallery for reference.
service_area: I service mostly mid - uptown areas but will travel if required.
products: I use only good quality products that have gained my trust over the years.
services: My services are: Paint/Stain and Plastering/Drywall/Taping- that includes restoration of old houses and new construction. I am a magician at hiding damages (no wallpaper or stucco). Woodworking - such as deck, stairs, railing, fences, porch code upgrading. Custom builds for personal use. Consult with design options. I can solve/troubleshoot difficult problems in certain situations. Water leak detection and restoration. Tiles, design & paint murals and window film treatments. Installer of many products. Basic wiring and plumbing too etc..
specialities: My specialties would be keeping an eye on the details as they can become overlooked and the over-all finish of the project at hand. I can help design & advise on small custom builds and paint/stain choices. Re-use, Re-claim or Re-purpose if necessary. I don't take liberties and give 100%. I also have a Home Inspectors certificate which gives me added knowledge to advise clients and troubleshoot issues & problems.

profile:
Aaron Ferguson’s passion has always been carpentry. It’s a craft I learned ‘on-the-job’ working for my Father’s landscaping company. The first contract was to install cabinets for a general contractor. Word soon spread about the company's work ethic, and our service offering expanded to interior trim, framing and siding. By 2005, we needed to hire full-time employees to help him deliver our services to an ever expanding list of satisfied clients. Our reputation attracted designers and builders of higher-end homes from across Toronto, the GTA and York Region.
Evergreen Carpentry now enjoys a reputation as the go-to option for contractors, builders and homeowners when they want top quality trim and siding products and workmanship. But many things remain the same as when Aaron decided to take that first job:
Work With Passion
Demonstrate Excellence in Execution Service
Safety First Always

profile:
Interior & Exterior Fine Finish Carpentry( cornice, dado & shaker panel mould,wainscoting, doors, baseboard, casing, etc) and Custom Cabinetry ( built-in's, entertainment units, custom kitchens, fireplace mantle's etc.). 
Welcome to the Website of Ewen Cameron Master Carpenter & Cabinetmaker: “EWEN MCC”
Having started my apprenticeship in July of 1980, I have been serving the GTA and Southern Ontario as a tradesman since 1985 and have been an Independent Businessman since 2001.
My goal in business has always been a simple one, to provide my clientele with professional quality fine carpentry and millwork, and with first-rate, personalized client services.
I provide my clients with a complete CONSULT-DESIGN-BUILD service.
Simply stated, I come and consult with you regarding the work you wish to have performed. Together, we then formulate a design. The canvas from which I can build can be as simple as a hand-drawn sketch outline, a picture from a design, or any other magazine, or a full set of blueprints. With many clients, they will simply tell me their vision and I will build it. Much of the work you will see in this web site is built from the client sketching a few lines on a wall and explaining how they envision the final piece. My experience allows me to obtain a sense of the client’s personal tastes and likes with regard to the type of architectural style they are seeking, be it modern, contemporary, traditional or anywhere in between.
At Ewen MCC, there are no middlemen to confuse the message. When you meet and speak with me, you are speaking with the person who shall be doing the work. No more missed small details, as there are no details too small, no more mis-measurements.
As you will see on the testimonials page, the respect of my clients home, or business, is of paramount importance to me.
I believe that my hard work and dedication has paid off, with the result being a lengthy list of very pleased clients.
